Sep 5 2006 	Great Value nice area	A lot more than we expected for a hotel in Manhattan. In a nice, quaint area - close to Chinatown, Financial District and ferries. Great value - 4 of us stayed for $180/night. Rooms and bathrooms were clean and staff (specifically John at the Front desk) were nice. Ask for a room with a view of the Brooklyn Bridge.	
