Apr 17 2006	Not Bad Enough to Leave Not Good Enough to Return	We paid $175 through priceline---, a good price for a New York hotel. The room was fine--a refrigerator, TV, closet. Having read previous reviews which complained of the noise from the streets, I asked--and received--a room facing the courtyard. Hence noise was not a problem. The continental breakfast was modest but sufficient.What was a problem was a bathroom sink that provided only a trickle of water. It was nearly impossible to shave or wash your face. I brought this to the attention of the desk attendant, who said it would be fixed, but nothing happened. Also, the temperature in the room was too warm, and trying to cool it, using the air conditioner, was unsuccessful. Fortunately we only stayed there two nights.Not recommended.	
Mar 12 2006	Great price great location	we stayed in seaport inn last year for 7 days, just after easter. the hotel is located just near the brooklyn brige in the beautiful part of ny called south street seaport, different from all the manhattan: small buildings, great shops, great restaurants, pear with beautiful riverfront cafes and a port with old ships and famous fish market. allthought the brige and fish market are close to the hotel there are no noise, we didn't heard a thing! from the hotel you can walk to the Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island ferries, the entire Financial District, Little Italy and China Town. the hotel is small and confortable, very clean, has 3 stars and deserves it. the staf is willing to help anytime. very good thing is breakfast which is included to price, nothing special but enough for tourist start of the day.overall i can say that we were very satisfied, there were 5 of us in one room for 6 nights and we payed 1200 euros with breakfast for everything.we're looking forward to visit again!	
Jan 29 2006	A Positive Experience	I just stayed at the Best Western at the South Street Seaport. I had an extremely positive experience. I was visiting my daughter in Brooklyn and wanted to stay at a hotel which wasn't too far from her residence. I had previously stayed at the Brooklyn Marriott, which was nice, but way too expensive. I stayed at the Best Western for a week and felt very comfortable there. The hotel is smallish with few services. However, the room was extremely clean, quiet and comfortable. It appeared to be freshly redecorated. The carpet and upolstery were spotless. My room looked over the street and was very quiet. Although I did not have too much interaction with the staff, when I did they were very pleasant. The complimentary breakfast was fine-a typical continental, but with enough variety, to find something to eat. Compared to other NY city hotels that I have stayed in, the value of the room was excellent. The location is probably not the most convenient for sightseeing in midtown, but for my needs it was perfect.I would definitely stay there again!	
Jan 10 2006	Awful - Never Again	We stayed here for a week over the New Year.We had arranged to pay by credit card. After 5 days, our cards were &quot;stopped&quot; due to the number and nature of transactions requested by the hotel. Having used my credit card in many hotels across the world, this has never happened to me.When I brought this to his attention, I found the Manager to be unhelpful and unapologetic - despite the fact that it was due to the hotel that we were in this situation. He did not provide a reasonable or detailed explanation for those transactions.He could not find any record of our checking in and initially was unable to find a record of my reservation. He also stated that the cost of our stay was almost $400 more than what I had booked.Resolving this took almost a full day (out of a 7 day holiday).Other Issues:While I was aware that it was not a great location, I was not aware that it was such a distance from the nearest sub-way station.On arrival we were allocated a room without a King Size bed (which I had booked) or views of the water/bridge (requested). On request, we were moved to a room with a king-size bed (still no views!)There was a strong smell of cigarette smoke in the room, despite it being a non-smoking room.	
