Oct 17 2005	Great value	Stayed over a weekend. Hotel is very convenient to Ground Zero, Battery Park, and Wall Street, all of which are within walking distance. Short cab ride into Little Italy or Chinatown.Rooms are small but nicely appointed and very quiet. Continental breakfast was good, newspaper and more substantial food at the deli next door. The Fulton fish market adds color and odor in the early morning but is pretty much closed by 9:00 or 10:00.You'll have to walk a block or two to get a cab. Be sure to take a card with the hotel address...we had three taxi drivers that did not know where the hotel was located.$200 for this room is a bargain in New York.	
Oct 6 2005	The most romantic and fabulous weekend of my life	My husband chose this hotel to propose to me in. He got a room with a beautiful balcony and we sat out there under the Brooklyn Bridge looking out on the East River and he popped the question. The hotel staff knew in advance that he was going to propose and made everything so wonderful. They were so accommodating and helpful to my husband leading up to the big night. I will always have fond memories of the staff and my time there.	
Sep 4 2005 	Nice budget hotel	Convenient location to NYU dorm. The evening desk clerk (Leon) was delightful. (better than most concierges at higher priced hotels.) The rest of the staff was okay. I had a 6th floor room with a huge balcony with a gorgeous view of the Brooklyn bridge. Room was adequate (big by NYC standards), bedspreads and curtains a little dated, thin towels, fiberglass jacuzzi. This not a luxury hotel but a good deal for the area. It was also very quiet. A bit of a hike to the nearest subway station, seaport is right next store with the typical retailers (jcrew, gap, etc.) It served the purpose of my visit (moving my daughter into NYU housing.)If you want to be near the action or need thicker towels, stay uptown.l	
Jul 21 2005	Great hotel!!!	We have just returned from our trip to NYC - we stayed at this hotel based on reviews posted here. We travelled with our children (9 and 12) and we were VERY impressed with this hotel. The staff were very helpful, the rooms were great, the beds were comfortable and everything was CLEAN. The complimentary breakfast was suitable and the coffee was actually good!This hotel is located at the seaport where there is a very busy fish market from midnight to 6:00 a.m everyday.....we stayed for 3 nights and did not hear a thing! The only evidence of the activity was the fishy smell when we stepped outside in the morning and all of the busy city workers cleaning and scrubbing the streets.Because this hotel is located away from the hustle and bustle of the city it appeared many of the guests were there on business. If you want to be a part of the Times Square chaous it is approx a $20 cab fare away, or an easy ride on a city bus.We will go back to the city and we will stay at this hotel again. I would be happy to respond to any emails regarding our stay.	
Jul 18 2005	Hotel Staff the best	Stayed there with two elderly parents and three teenagers, we all loved it. The attentive staff were helpful and thoughtful. Touches like that take an average hotel up a couple of notches. The rooms were clean and comfortable after a long day of sightseeing.	
Jun 26 2005	Very satisfied!	We stayed at the Seaport Inn in June 2005, and I must say that I was pleasantly surprised. After reading mixed online reviews, I didn't know what to expect. We found the exterior of the hotel to be quaint and well-tended. The lobby is small, but clean and comfortable. We had absolutely no problem with the staff, who graciously accomodated our early arrival, late checkout, and requests for extra towels and pillows. Housekeeping services were great, as well. The hotel even has a small fitness room.Our room with two queen beds was VERY CLEAN and spacious. The room was equipped with a table and 2 upholstered chairs, two upholstered &quot;benches&quot;, an iron/ironing board, hair dryer, coffee maker, refrigerator, a generous amount of toiletries, large tv, a nintendo system and high speed internet. The carpet, beds, and all furnishings were in excellent repair, and did I mention clean?The room rate includes breakfast, which consisted of bagels, croissants, breads, fruit cups, fruit, yogurt, cereal milk, juice and coffee. The breakfast room is smallish, but we brought our food back to the room, anyway.The hotel's Lower Manhattan location is convenient to WTC site, the Seaport, and Battery Park. There are many restaurants, shops and a drug store within walking distance. The hotel is near the Seaport, so be prepared for a intermittant &quot;fishy&quot; smell when outdoors. The hotel does not have a restaurant, gift shop or offer room service like some of the higher cost places, but who cares? We felt comfortable, safe and completely satisfied with our hotel choice. This one is a winner!	
