Jun 1 2005 	Simple and basic but a good choice	An interesting hotel for New York City, this property is down the street from the South Street Seaport, a tourist destination. It's also close to the financial district, and not too far from Chinatown and Little Italy. It's a bit removed from the main streets and the neighborhood is a bit industrial, so at night it appears creepy, but it's not at all. There's not too much to eat in the immediate vicinity, but a short walk can get you decent food. The check in was easy, and the rooms are basic but perfectly fine. Some have very nice views of the Brooklyn Bridge and the river. Free, basic breakfast in the morning, and a small gym too. If all you need is a room and don't want to pay typical &quot;midtown&quot; prices for being close to the theater/shopping action, consider this property.	
